{"type":"message","id":"0d9a58fc","parentId":"3d188475","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:53:20.370Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tpqexytqephy_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 075218\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and insights:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. The key insight is that Compression and Causal Discovery are the same problem\r\n3. The next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n\r\nThe pending action is:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nI need to implement the TIC classifier. This is a new experiment that will analyze the pulse logs to find invariant (stable) vs variant (changing) patterns.\r\n\r\nLet me first look at what's in the logs directory to understand the structure of pulse logs, then implement the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nI'll create a new file `research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md` that documents the experiment design and implementation approach. Or I could directly implement the classifier.\r\n\r\nActually, I should implement the actual TIC classifier. Let me check what the pulse logs look like and then implement the classifier.\r\n\r\nFirst, let me understand the current state by looking at what exists in the research directory and logs.\r\n\r\nSince this is a stateless discontinuous agent, each pulse is fresh. I should:\r\n1. Create the TIC classifier implementation\r\n2. Run it against the pulse logs\r\n3. Document the results\r\n\r\nLet me create the TIC classifier. I'll make it a Python script that:\r\n1. Loads all pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant elements (things that don't change across pulses)\r\n3. Identifies variant elements (things that change)\r\n4. Tests classification accuracy\r\n5. Predicts next pulse content from invariants\r\n6. Reports metrics against success criteria\r\n\r\nI'll create: `scripts/tic_classifier.py` - a Python script that implements the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me write this out:\r\n\r\n\r\nThe classifier will load the pulse logs, extract text patterns from each one, then distinguish between elements that remain stable across sessions versus those that shift. I'll compute metrics on how well the system separates invariants from variants, test whether invariants can reliably predict what comes next, and measure whether the accuracy meets the defined thresholds.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next logical step to validate the Compression-Causal Duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic_classifier.py` - a Python script implementing the TIC experiment that will analyze pulse logs, classify content as invariant/variant, and measure prediction accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple, Set\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs() -> List[Dict]:\r\n    \"\"\"Load all pulse logs from logs directory.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = []\r\n    for f in sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n        with open(f, 'r') as fp:\r\n            content = fp.read()\r\n            logs.append({\r\n                'file': f.name,\r\n                'content': content,\r\n                'lines': content.split('\\n')\r\n            })\r\n    return logs\r\n\r\ndef extract_elements(logs: List[Dict]) -> Dict[str, List[str]]:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structural elements from logs.\"\"\"\r\n    elements = {\r\n        'headings': [],  # H1, H2, H3 lines\r\n        'checkboxes': [],  # - [ ] or - [x] lines\r\n        'filepaths': [],  # paths like research/*.md, scripts/*.py\r\n        'goals': [],  # lines starting with - or * \r\n        'quoted': [],  # lines with > prefix\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    for log in logs:\r\n        for line in log['lines']:\r\n            stripped = line.strip()\r\n            # Headings\r\n            if re.match(r'^#{1,3}\\s+', stripped):\r\n                elements['headings'].append(stripped)\r\n            # Checkboxes\r\n            if re.match(r'^-\\s+\\[[ xX]\\]\\s+', stripped):\r\n                elements['checkboxes'].append(stripped)\r\n            # File paths\r\n            for path in re.findall(r'[\\w\\-\\./]+\\.(md|py|ps1|txt)', stripped):\r\n                elements['filepaths'].append(path)\r\n            # Goal lines\r\n            if re.match(r'^-\\s+', stripped) and '[' in stripped:\r\n                elements['goals'].append(stripped)\r\n            # Quoted\r\n            if stripped.startswith('>'):\r\n                elements['quoted'].append(stripped)\r\n    \r\n    return elements\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant_variant(elements: Dict[str, List[str]]) -> Dict[str, Tuple[Set, Set]]:\r\n    \"\"\"Classify elements as invariant (>80% persistence) or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    INVARIANT_THRESHOLD = 0.8\r\n    results = {}\r\n    \r\n    for elem_type, items in elements.items():\r\n        if not items:\r\n            continue\r\n        \r\n        # Count occurrences of each unique element\r\n        counts = defaultdict(int)\r\n        for item in items:\r\n            counts[item] += 1\r\n        \r\n        total = len(items)\r\n        invariants = set()\r\n        variants = set()\r\n        \r\n        for item, count in counts.items():\r\n            persistence = count / total\r\n            if persistence >= INVARIANT_THRESHOLD:\r\n                invariants.add(item)\r\n            else:\r\n                variants\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 07:52:50\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774353200368}}
